race.comment: INVASIVE DREAMS (9) returned an excellent figure when just behind the placings in a Randwick Saturday class race three back. Went close after that over this distance at Gosford but was a bit flat last time. Can bounce back in this suitable contest. NANTUCKET ISLAND (5) settled midfield then showed a nice turn of foot to score with a bit in reserve last time out over 1400m at Kembla. In career-best form this prep and the step up to a mile looks a perfect progression. MISS HADES (4) returned from a five-month spell with an encouraging effort over 1400m at Newcastle (metro), closing well but missing by a long neck at BM78 level. Will find this a lot easier but does go up 5kgs. Sure to give a good account. KINGSTON CHARM (3) is very good on her day but it has been a while between drinks. Nash's stand-over tactics may do the trick. IT'S A WONDER (2) has ability but generally needs the sting out of the ground to shine. Exotics inclusion only.
